This class has 6 places where it does this.

* addDateCondition(String, Collection)
* addDateCondition(String, Date[])
* addNumberCondition(String, Collection)
* addNumberCondition(String, Long[])
* addStringCondition(String, Collection)
* addStringCondition(String, String[])

In each place the pattern of the problem is similar and looks like
{code}
if ((dates != null) && (dates.size() == 1)) {
  return addDateCondition(clauseName, Operator.EQUALS, dates.iterator().next());
} else {
  return addDateCondition(clauseName, Operator.IN, dates);
}

public JqlClauseBuilder addDateCondition(...) {
  containsNoNulls("dates", dates);
  Assertions.not("dates is empty", dates.isEmpty());
...
{code}

In *addDateCondition* _dates_ has to be non-null. But in the first bit of code we clearly think there are reasons it could be null.

