We'd like a maximum distance between the longest label and its value of about 20-30 pixels.  There is no requirement that the right column in the Details block have the same label column width as the left column.

It may be beneficial to consider custom fields separately when calculating what the longest label is.  The custom fields can have its own internal "value" margin.

We've been wrestling with this since 4.1 so I know its not easy, but customers *are* sensitive to this and do not understand why our values float so far from our labels.

eg Penny's QA data holds some big fields (issue summary?).
These will fail to import on Oracle because the jiraissue.summary column is defined to be 255 bytes, but I think it needs to be 255 characters (for multi-byte chars).

Also note that I think there may be some separate sizing concerns - eg ofbiz fieldtype for Oracle defines
{noformat}
    <field-type-def type="very-long" sql-type="VARCHAR2(4000)" java-type="String"></field-type-def>
{noformat}
but MySQL defines:
{noformat}
    <field-type-def type="very-long" sql-type="TEXT" java-type="String"></field-type-def>
{noformat}

